              data-src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/hqzVw-O_HjonqQzRtLYj2s-g910t7gSeFJNGNTAc3OJCIDgTFvAEQ7LWW7MwhMdBaQMWYnKSRL4bY7y4gFQMmx90VQtz8w=w400-h300-c" alt="Orpheus &amp; Eurydice in the hands of a theatrical genius"
              data-srcset="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/hqzVw-O_HjonqQzRtLYj2s-g910t7gSeFJNGNTAc3OJCIDgTFvAEQ7LWW7MwhMdBaQMWYnKSRL4bY7y4gFQMmx90VQtz8w=w680-h480-c 480w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/hqzVw-O_HjonqQzRtLYj2s-g910t7gSeFJNGNTAc3OJCIDgTFvAEQ7LWW7MwhMdBaQMWYnKSRL4bY7y4gFQMmx90VQtz8w=w1360-h960-c 2x" alt="Orpheus &amp; Eurydice in the hands of a theatrical genius"
              ></picture><span class="post--meta"><em class="post--meta-date">March 14, 2018</em><em class="post--meta-author">Loren Lester</em><em class="post--meta-category">Review</em></span></a><p class="post--list-desc">Though he has a decades-long, international reputation for his ballets, Mr. Neumeier&#39;s ingenious and beautiful choreography is only part of the story, or rather &quot;his&quot; story. Writers are supposed to write what they know; in this case, Mr. Neumeier directs what he knows. This is the famous opera written by Gluck in 1774, but it&#39;s no longer the travel and travail of a musician.</p><a href="/orpheus-eurydice-in-the-hands-of-a-theatrical-genius/" class="btn post--button">Read More</a></li><li><a href="/jerry-springer-the-opera-hits-new-york/" class="post--list-title"><h1>Jerry Springer - The Opera hits New York</h1></a><a href="/jerry-springer-the-opera-hits-new-york/" class="post--list-image"><picture><!-- <source srcset="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-y1098InQ-qxb8g4WF9GJOvwBZsgoI98XZSR4PGC52WE9b7DO8vNmBat9DCujn4YiHZmd3W8B17hruxRaD7yhWTleJCoA=w680-h480-c 480w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-y1098InQ-qxb8g4WF9GJOvwBZsgoI98XZSR4PGC52WE9b7DO8vNmBat9DCujn4YiHZmd3W8B17hruxRaD7yhWTleJCoA=w1360-h960-c 2x" media="(min-width: 40em)"> --><img
