              data-src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-y1098InQ-qxb8g4WF9GJOvwBZsgoI98XZSR4PGC52WE9b7DO8vNmBat9DCujn4YiHZmd3W8B17hruxRaD7yhWTleJCoA=w400-h300-c" alt="Jerry Springer - The Opera hits New York"
              data-srcset="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-y1098InQ-qxb8g4WF9GJOvwBZsgoI98XZSR4PGC52WE9b7DO8vNmBat9DCujn4YiHZmd3W8B17hruxRaD7yhWTleJCoA=w680-h480-c 480w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-y1098InQ-qxb8g4WF9GJOvwBZsgoI98XZSR4PGC52WE9b7DO8vNmBat9DCujn4YiHZmd3W8B17hruxRaD7yhWTleJCoA=w1360-h960-c 2x" alt="Jerry Springer - The Opera hits New York"
              ></picture><span class="post--meta"><em class="post--meta-date">March 13, 2018</em><em class="post--meta-author">John Hohmann</em><em class="post--meta-category">Review</em></span></a><p class="post--list-desc">But why be churlish when songs like &quot;Diaper Man,&quot; &quot;Him Am The Devil&quot; and the production number, &quot;This is My KKK Moment,&quot; tune up this gleefully lewd production? In fact, you would be advised to just sit back and be a complicit member of the audience that comes pre-stocked with an immensely talented group of misfits longing for their 15 seconds of fame.</p><a href="/jerry-springer-the-opera-hits-new-york/" class="btn post--button">Read More</a></li><li><a href="/heavy-on-the-plot-points-the-great-god-pan/" class="post--list-title"><h1>Heavy on the plot points: The Great God Pan</h1></a><a href="/heavy-on-the-plot-points-the-great-god-pan/" class="post--list-image"><picture><!-- <source srcset="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/lIHJDwR8HgpjzB3hpM2iYuWDeHwErIDlOwLoRueYhi2dxrp-hKp9ZGz8FF1QMsNLRw-q9uRigeEeN9_BmOFV_rgJfXij=w680-h480-c 480w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/lIHJDwR8HgpjzB3hpM2iYuWDeHwErIDlOwLoRueYhi2dxrp-hKp9ZGz8FF1QMsNLRw-q9uRigeEeN9_BmOFV_rgJfXij=w1360-h960-c 2x" media="(min-width: 40em)"> --><img
