              ></picture><span class="post--meta"><em class="post--meta-date">March 13, 2018</em><em class="post--meta-author">Jenna Simeonov</em><em class="post--meta-category">Interview</em></span></a><p class="post--list-desc">&quot;The singing can sound silly to some at first, because it is a very intense, open sound, but with some of the best music ever written in the hands of a skilled artist, live music can bypass the intellect and resonate directly with the soul and heart.&quot;</p><a href="/kyra-millan-making-opera-for-all-ages/" class="btn post--button">Read More</a></li><li><a href="/talking-with-singers-stephanie-blythe/" class="post--list-title"><h1>Talking with singers: Stephanie Blythe</h1></a><a href="/talking-with-singers-stephanie-blythe/" class="post--list-image"><picture><!-- <source srcset="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/PFQSrk5ZzPqJoc2yb0Cfa9os7TuuPQLx_Lvj3gGHWS5EQFFy32Kz--IbiMmKrI7wOfiZVbd2xWq-8ZvLmBnM1NfkRsF58g=w680-h480-c 480w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/PFQSrk5ZzPqJoc2yb0Cfa9os7TuuPQLx_Lvj3gGHWS5EQFFy32Kz--IbiMmKrI7wOfiZVbd2xWq-8ZvLmBnM1NfkRsF58g=w1360-h960-c 2x" media="(min-width: 40em)"> --><img
