              ></picture><span class="post--meta"><em class="post--meta-date">March 12, 2018</em><em class="post--meta-author">Jenna Simeonov</em><em class="post--meta-category">Interview</em></span></a><p class="post--list-desc">Blythe approaches her recital work with a refreshingly casual air, as though she doesn&#39;t confuse her passion with taking it all too seriously. She has even graced the recital stage with her ukulele in hand, a more recent passion-project of hers. &quot;I just did a recital in New York; here we are in Merkin Hall, singing &#39;Don&#39;t Fence Me In&#39; and I was accompanying on ukulele.&quot;</p><a href="/talking-with-singers-stephanie-blythe/" class="btn post--button">Read More</a></li><li><a href="/celebrating-bernstein-in-chicago-how-can-one-not-be-enchanted/" class="post--list-title"><h1>Celebrating Bernstein in Chicago: &quot;How can one not be enchanted?&quot;</h1></a><a href="/celebrating-bernstein-in-chicago-how-can-one-not-be-enchanted/" class="post--list-image"><picture><!-- <source srcset="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/aNFCj1PePmajaCR7RMBjQBMToXqXeQpD-8IEwTiTuFWGNKsKNoAMha6w1fmdyMgRoopRv1uM0h01UfsrgKGdW7sJx6I=w680-h480-c 480w, https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/aNFCj1PePmajaCR7RMBjQBMToXqXeQpD-8IEwTiTuFWGNKsKNoAMha6w1fmdyMgRoopRv1uM0h01UfsrgKGdW7sJx6I=w1360-h960-c 2x" media="(min-width: 40em)"> --><img
              class="lazyload"
              src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/aNFCj1PePmajaCR7RMBjQBMToXqXeQpD-8IEwTiTuFWGNKsKNoAMha6w1fmdyMgRoopRv1uM0h01UfsrgKGdW7sJx6I=w40-h30-c"
              data-src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/aNFCj1PePmajaCR7RMBjQBMToXqXeQpD-8IEwTiTuFWGNKsKNoAMha6w1fmdyMgRoopRv1uM0h01UfsrgKGdW7sJx6I=w400-h300-c" alt="Celebrating Bernstein in Chicago: &quot;How can one not be enchanted?&quot;"
