              ></picture><span class="post--meta"><em class="post--meta-date">March 12, 2018</em><em class="post--meta-author">Michael Pecak</em><em class="post--meta-category">Review</em></span></a><p class="post--list-desc">How can one not be enchanted? This is the same Bernstein-ian smile I recognize in my teachers&#39; recollections of their mentor, the same smile that, to my ears, permeates his whole artistic output, and the same smile that suffused the Lyric Opera of Chicago&#39;s commemorative Bernstein concert this past Saturday at the Lyric Opera House.</p><a href="/celebrating-bernstein-in-chicago-how-can-one-not-be-enchanted/" class="btn post--button">Read More</a></li></ul><ul class="paginator"><li class="active"><a href="/">1</a></li><li><a href="/page-2/">2</a></li><li><a href="/page-3/">3</a></li><li>...</li><li><a href="/page-172/">172</a></li><li class="next"><a href="/page-2/"><span>Older Posts</span><i class="icon-arrow-right"></i></a></li></ul>
